The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Croatia upset United States 
Zagreb: Croatia pulled off a major upset beating the United States in the first round of the World Group Davis Cup match at Zagreb Sunday. In the first reverse singles of the day, Ivan Ljubicic beat James Blake 6-3, 6-7, 6-4, 6-3 to ensure an unlikely victory for the hosts. Earlier, Saturday, injured Goran Ivanisevic paired up with Ivan Ljubicic to beat the American pair of James Blake and Mardy Fish 3-6, 4-6, 7-6, 6-4, 6-4.  Results (Reverse Singles):  In Bucharest: France bt Romania 4-1 (Nicolas Escude bt Gabriel Trifu 7-6, 4-6, 6-4; Fabrice Santoro lost to Victor Hanescu 6-1, 6-4. In Zagreb: Croatia bt US 3-1 (Ivan Ljubicic bt James Blake 6-3, 6-7, 6-4, 6-3) In Ostrava: Czech Republic 2 Russia 2 (when reports last came in) (Jiri Novak bt Yevgeny Kafelnikov 6-2, 6-3, 7-6 In Arnhem: Switzerland bt The Netherlands 3-2 (Michel Kratochvil bt Martin Verkerk 1-6, 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (8-6) 1-6; Roger Federer bt Sjeng Schalken 7-6 (7-2), 6-4, 7-5. In Buenos Aires: Argentina bt Germany 5-0 (Juan Ignacio Chela bt David Prinosil 6-4, 6-1; Gaston Gaudio bt Lars Burgsmuller 6-3 6-1) In Sydney: Australia bt England 4-1 (wayne Arthurs bt Miles Maclagan 4-6, 6-1, 6-4; Todd Woodrbridge lost to Alex Bogdanovic 2-6, 6-7) In Seville: Spain bt Belgium 5-0 (Carlos Ferrero bt Kristof Vliegen 6-1, 6-4; Carlos Moya bt Christophe Rochus 6-2, 6-2.  (Reuters)  Copyright 
